<section epub:type="appendix" role="doc-appendix" data-index="3">
<header data-index="4">
<h1 data-index="5"><a id="start" data-index="6"></a><span epub:type="pagebreak" role="doc-pagebreak" title="E-1" id="Page_E-1" data-index="7"></span><span class="chapterNumber" data-index="8"><span class="codeColorGreen2" data-index="9">Appendix</span> E</span> <br data-index="10"><span class="chapterTitle" data-index="11"><span class="codeColorGreen2" data-index="12">Specimen Financial Statements: <span class="red" data-index="13">Marks and Spencer plc</span></span></span></h1>
</header>
<section id="a05-sec-0002" data-index="14">
<p data-index="15"><span class="red" data-index="16">Marks and Spencer (M&amp;S) plc</span> is one of the United Kingdom's leading retailers, with over 1,330 stores worldwide. The company is committed to delivering sustainable, highquality food, clothing, and home products.</p>
<figure data-index="17">
<img class="center" src="https://ereader-books-prod.chegg.com/682/9781119503682/39c53495-be04-40a4-af01-80a39a7df223/OPS/images/BM/t0010.jpg" alt="A table titled 'Consolidated Income Statement' shows the data for two time periods: 53 weeks ended 1 April 2017 and 53 weeks ended 2 April 2016. The table has four main columns: the first column displays the particulars, the second column shows the reference to notes, the third and the fourth column show the data for the 2017 and 2016. The sub‐columns for the third and the fourth column are: underlying million pounds, non‐underlying million pounds, and total million pounds. The data in the table is given as follows.
Revenue at the beginning with reference to notes 2 and 3 shows the amount for 2017 as: Underlying, 10,622, Total, 10,622; and the amount for 2016 as: Underlying, 10,555.4, Total, 10,555.4.
Operating profit with reference to notes 2,3, and 5 shows the amount for 2017 as: Underlying, 690.6, Non‐underlying, negative 437.4, Total, 23.2; and the amount for 2016 as: Underlying, 784.9, Non‐underlying, negative 200.8, Total, 584.1.
Items under operating profit are:
Finance income: Note, 6; 2017: Underlying, 36.2, Total, 36.2; 2016: Underlying, 21.1, Total, 21.1.
Finance cost: Note, 6; 2017: Underlying, negative 113.0, Total, negative 113.0; 2016: Underlying, 116.4, Total, 116.4.
Adding the items results in the profit before tax: notes, 4 and 5; 2017: Underlying, 613.8, Non‐underlying, negative 437.4, Total, 176.4; 2016: Underlying, 689.6, Non‐underlying, negative 200.8, Total, 488.8.
The income tax expense with reference to note 7, the values are given as: 2017: Underlying, negative 122.4, Non‐underlying, 61.7, Total, negative 60.7; 2016: Underlying, negative 118.8, Non‐underlying, 34.4, Total, negative 84.4.
Therefore, the profit for the year, 2017 is shown as: Underlying, 491.4, Non‐underlying, negative 375.7, Total, 115.7; and for 2016 is shown as: Underlying, 570.8, Non‐underlying, negative 166.4, Total, 404.4.
The next section titled 'Attributable to:' shows the following items with their amounts:
Owners of the parent: 2017: Underlying, 492.8, Non‐underlying, negative 375.7, Total, 117.1; 2016: Underlying, 573.3, Non‐underlying, negative 166.4, Total, 409.6.
Non‐controlling interests: 2017: Underlying, negative 1.4, Total, negative 1.4; 2016: Underlying, negative 2.5, Total, negative 2.5.
Cumulative total is given as: 2017: Underlying, 491.4, Non‐underlying, negative 375.7, Total, 115.7; 2016: Underlying, 570.8, Non‐underlying, negative 166.4, Total, 404.4.
The end of the table shows the basic earning per share, with reference to note 8: 2017: Underlying, 30.4 pence, Total, 7.2 pence; 2016: Underlying, 35.0 pence, Total, 24.9 pence. And the diluted earnings per share, with reference to note 8 are: 2017: Underlying, 30.2 pence, Total, 7.2 pence; 2016: Underlying, 34.9 pence, Total, 24.8 pence." data-index="18" data-size="%7B%22width%22%3A659%2C%22height%22%3A800%7D">
</figure>
<p data-index="19"><br data-index="20"></p>
<figure data-index="21">
<img class="center" src="https://ereader-books-prod.chegg.com/682/9781119503682/39c53495-be04-40a4-af01-80a39a7df223/OPS/images/BM/t0011.jpg" alt="A table titled Consolidated Statement Income Statement shows a table divided into four columns to present the data for the time periods, the statement covers, 53 weeks ended 1 April 2017 and 53 weeks ended 2 April 2016. The amounts are given in million pounds.
The first section, Profit for the year shows amount 115.7 for 2017 and 404.4 for 2016. The next section, Other comprehensive income shows items that will not be reclassified to profit or loss having two entries as follows:
Remeasurements of retirement benefit schemes, reference to note 11: negative 68.9; 346.2.
Tax charge or (credit) on items that will not be reclassified: 25.3; negative 45.6.
The total items that will not be reclassified to profit or loss is: negative 43.6; 300.6.
The items that will be reclassified subsequently to profit or loss, with amounts for 1 April 2017 and 2 April 2016 are given as follows:
Foreign currency translation differences: 31.0; 7.3.
Cash flow hedges and net investment hedges shows the following items and their amounts:
fair value movements recognized in other comprehensive income: 56.1, negative 30.1;
reclassified and reported in profit or loss: negative 72.4, negative 22.1; amount recognized in inventories: negative 20.1, 5.9;
The Tax credit on cash flow hedges and net investment hedges is 4.1 for 1 April 2017 and 6.5 for 2 April 2016.
The total of the items that will be reclassified subsequently to profit or loss are: negative 1.3, negative 32.5.
The next line shows the Other comprehensive (expense) or income for the year, net of tax as: negative 44.9, 268.1.
Therefore, the total comprehensive income for the year is: 70.8 for 1 April 2017 and 672.5 for 2 April 2016.
The last lines of the income statement displays that the income is attributable to:
Owners of the parent: 72.2 for 1 April 2017 and 675.0 for 2 April 2016.
Non‐controlling interests: negative 1.4 for 1 April 2017 and negative 2.5 for 2 April 2016.
The total of attributable income is 70.8 for 1 April 2017 and negative 672.5 for 2 April 2016." data-index="22" data-size="%7B%22width%22%3A277%2C%22height%22%3A323%7D">
