<figure data-index="26">
<img class="center" src="https://ereader-books-prod.chegg.com/682/9781119503682/39c53495-be04-40a4-af01-80a39a7df223/OPS/images/BM/t0012.jpg" alt="A table titled Consolidated Statement of Financial Position is divided into four columns, as at 1 April 2017 and 2 April 2016, the amount given in million pounds. There are three sections: Assets, Liabilities, and Equity. There are three columns; the first column shows the particulars and the last two columns show the respective amounts under column headers 1 April 2017 and 2 April 2016.
The Asset section shows Non‐current Assets listed with entries as follows:
Intangible assets, reference to note 14: 709.0, 802.8;
Property, plant and equipment reference to note 15: 4,837.8, 5,027.1;
